Hi,

yes....I am indexing into Solr 4.1.

It depends how you crawl and what you want to index.
Basically all you need to do is to open the warc files and read them 
record by record, extract the information you want (this all can be done 
with the java library that come with Heritrix) to index and then use the 
SolrJ API to add the data to your index. This all done in Java.

I think you can write your own Heritrix extension which writes directly 
into the index too.
We thought about doing it this way first but we prefer to have the warc 
files so I can recreate the index without crawling the websites again.

Regards,
Markus


